{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775877182193,"sessionID":"ses_2857a4700ffe1IXDyt1nODT0cT","part":{"id":"prt_d7a85c33200117YX5jTQphcjXt","messageID":"msg_d7a85b9f8001kKZh1Zov6pY5Qp","sessionID":"ses_2857a4700ffe1IXDyt1nODT0cT","type":"tool","tool":"task","callID":"call_bd569f708dfd40ca9f56dc33","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"description":"Explore agentcube project structure","prompt":"Explore the agentcube project at /home/dsj/benchmark to understand:\n1. The overall project structure (top-level directories and key files)\n2. Whether there's an existing Makefile or any build system\n3. What AR-033 or similar AR documents exist (search for AR-*.md or similar)\n4. Any existing tasks.md or planning documents\n5. What the project does (look at README, package.json, go.mod, or similar)\n\nReturn a comprehensive summary of the project structure, existing build system (if any), and any relevant AR documents or planning files.","subagent_type":"explore"},"output":"task_id: ses_2857a3093ffeUKIVE8cM3B3RaD (for resuming to continue this task if needed)\n\n<task_result>\nNow I have a comprehensive picture of the project. Here is the full summary:\n\n---\n\n## Comprehensive Project Summary: SDD-TEE (SDD Token Efficiency Evaluation)\n\n### 1. Project Overview\n\nThis is **not** the agentcube project itself. Rather, it is a **benchmark/evaluation framework** called **SDD-TEE** that measures token efficiency when using Specification-Driven Development (SDD) to rebuild the real open-source project [agentcube](https://github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube) (a Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform for AI agents).\n\nThe framework decomposes agentcube into **43 granular ARs (Allocated Requirements)** and runs each through a complete 8-stage SDD workflow (`/opsx:new` -> `/opsx:ff` -> `/opsx:apply` -> `/opsx:verify` -> `/opsx:archive`), quantifying token consumption across 8 stages x 5 dimensions.\n\n### 2. Top-Level Directory Structure\n\n```\n/home/dsj/benchmark/\n|-- Makefile                    # Unified entry point (all operations via make)\n|-- README.md                   # Project documentation (Chinese + English)\n|-- PLAN.md                     # Implementation plan for AR-023 through AR-033 (1441 lines)\n|-- PROPOSAL.md                 # Evaluation system design document (Chinese)\n|-- proposal.md                 # AR-032 Dockerfile multi-stage build proposal\n|-- task.md                     # Original task description (Chinese)\n|-- requirements.txt            # Python dependencies (pyyaml, litellm, matplotlib, rich)\n|-- configs/\n|   |-- config.yaml\n|   |-- litellm_config.yaml     # LiteLLM Proxy routing configuration\n|-- docs/\n|   |-- SDD开发Token消耗度量指标体系设计方案.md  # Metrics design spec (Chinese)\n|-- specs/                      # 43 AR spec files organized by domain\n|   |-- project.md              # OpenSpec project context for agentcube\n|   |-- test_spec.md\n|   |-- ci-cd/                  # spec.md, design.md\n|   |-- cli-toolkit/            # spec.md, design.md\n|   |-- code-execution/         # spec.md, design.md\n|   |-- deployment/             # spec.md, design.md, client-go.md\n|   |-- idle-cleanup/           # spec.md, design.md\n|   |-- integrations/           # spec.md, design.md\n|   |-- python-sdk/             # spec.md, design.md\n|   |-- sandbox-orchestration/  # spec.md, design.md, AR-005-sandbox-creation-processor/\n|   |-- session-routing/        # spec.md, design.md\n|   |-- session-store/          # spec.md, design.md\n|   |-- testing/                # agentcube_tdd_manifest.md\n|-- scripts/                    # Core benchmark engine and tooling\n|   |-- engine.py               # Main benchmark driver (v5.1)\n|   |-- auditor.py              # LiteLLM JSONL token auditor\n|   |-- schema.py               # Data schema validation\n|   |-- report.py               # HTML report generation\n|   |-- compare.py              # Cross-run comparison\n|   |-- export.py               # CSV/JSON/Markdown export\n|   |-- preflight.py            # Environment validation\n|   |-- validate.py\n|   |-- aggregate.py\n|   |-- equivalence.py\n|   |-- run_benchmark.sh        # Single benchmark entry\n|   |-- batch_benchmark.sh      # Batch benchmark entry\n|   |-- adapters/\n|       |-- base.py             # StageRecord + BaseAdapter\n|       |-- claude_code.py      # Claude Code adapter\n|       |-- gemini_cli.py       # Gemini CLI adapter\n|       |-- cursor_cli.py       # Cursor CLI adapter\n|       |-- opencode_cli.py     # OpenCode CLI adapter\n|-- sdk-python/                 # AgentCube Python SDK (the thing being built)\n|   |-- pyproject.toml          # agentcube-sdk v0.1.0\n|   |-- agentcube/              # SDK source code\n|   |-- tests/\n|-- workspaces/                 # Per-run isolated code workspaces (13 runs)\n|   |-- v5.1/\n|       |-- claude-code_claude-sonnet-4_* (4 runs)\n|       |-- opencode-cli_* (multiple models: qwen3.6-plus, glm-4.7, glm-5, kimi-k2.5, MiniMax-M2.5, qwen3.5-plus)\n|-- results/\n    |-- runs/                   # _full.json + logs per run (v1.0 through v5.1)\n    |-- reports/                # HTML reports (v1.0 through v5.1 + latest)\n    |-- project_analysis/\n```\n\n### 3. Build System\n\n**Yes, there is a comprehensive Makefile** at `/home/dsj/benchmark/Makefile` (97 lines). Key targets:\n\n| Target | Description |\n|--------|-------------|\n| `setup` | Install Python dependencies |\n| `preflight` | Verify environment (tool + model) |\n| `proxy` | Start LiteLLM Proxy on port 4000 |\n| `run-v51` | Run single benchmark (TOOL + MODEL) |\n| `run-v51-proxy` | Run through LiteLLM Proxy |\n| `run-v51-dry` | Dry-run (test prompts, no API calls) |\n| `batch-v51` | Run all tool x model combinations |\n| `batch-v51-proxy` | Batch through LiteLLM Proxy |\n| `report-v51` | Generate report from latest run |\n| `compare-v51` | Cross-run comparison report |\n| `export-v51` | Export to CSV/JSON/Markdown |\n| `selftest` | Validate data against schema |\n| `mock` | Generate mock data report |\n| `clean-v51` / `clean` | Remove generated results |\n\nThe project also uses **Python packaging** via `requirements.txt` and `sdk-python/pyproject.toml` (setuptools-based, agentcube-sdk v0.1.0).\n\n### 4. AR Documents (AR-033 and Similar)\n\n**No standalone AR-*.md files exist** as individual files in the repository. However, AR documents are embedded in two key locations:\n\n1. **`/home/dsj/benchmark/PLAN.md`** -- This is the primary AR document. It contains detailed implementation plans for **AR-023 through AR-033** (11 ARs, 78 files total), including:\n   - AR-023: Dify Plugin Manifest and Provider Structure\n   - AR-024: Dify Tool Schema and Implementation\n   - AR-025: PCAP Analyzer FastAPI Service\n   - AR-026: Helm Chart -- Workload Manager Templates\n   - AR-027: Helm Chart -- Router Templates\n   - AR-028: Helm Chart -- CRDs and Optional Volcano Scheduler\n   - AR-029: Dockerfiles and Makefile Build Targets\n   - AR-030: GitHub Actions CI/CD Pipelines\n   - AR-031: CLI Toolkit -- Pack and Build Commands\n   - AR-032: CLI Toolkit -- Publish, Invoke, Status Commands\n   - **AR-033: Python SDK -- Clients and Exceptions** (11 files, including `CodeInterpreterClient`, `AgentRuntimeClient`, exception hierarchy, control plane client, data plane clients, and utilities)\n\n2. **`/home/dsj/benchmark/proposal.md`** -- A detailed proposal specifically for **AR-032** (Dockerfile multi-stage builds for 3 images: Workload Manager, Router, picod).\n\n3. **`/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/sandbox-orchestration/AR-005-sandbox-creation-processor/`** -- An example of an AR-specific spec directory containing a `design.md` file.\n\nThe specs directory contains domain-level spec.md and design.md files (not per-AR), covering: ci-cd, cli-toolkit, code-execution, deployment, idle-cleanup, integrations, python-sdk, sandbox-orchestration, session-routing, session-store, and testing.\n\n### 5. Planning Documents\n\n| File | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/PLAN.md` | Detailed AR-023 to AR-033 implementation plan with file-by-file specs (1441 lines) |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/PROPOSAL.md` | SDD-TEE evaluation system design (Chinese, 189 lines) -- 5-dimension metrics, 8-stage workflow, baseline methodology |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/proposal.md` | AR-032 Dockerfile multi-stage build proposal (265 lines) |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/task.md` | Original task description (Chinese, 16 lines) |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/docs/SDD开发Token消耗度量指标体系设计方案.md` | Metrics system design spec (Chinese, 199 lines) |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/test_spec.md` | Test specification |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/testing/agentcube_tdd_manifest.md` | TDD manifest |\n\n**No `tasks.md` file exists** at the top level or anywhere in the project.\n\n### 6. What the Project Does\n\nThe project is a **benchmarking framework** that:\n\n1. Takes the real agentcube project (Go + Python Kubernetes sandbox platform) and decomposes it into 43 ARs\n2. Runs each AR through an 8-stage SDD workflow using various AI coding CLI tools (Claude Code, Gemini CLI, Cursor CLI, OpenCode CLI) and models (Claude Sonnet 4, Qwen 3.6-plus, GLM-5, GLM-4.7, Kimi K2.5, MiniMax M2.5, Qwen 3.5-plus)\n3. Tracks token consumption at every stage using LiteLLM Proxy as the authoritative data source\n4. Measures 5 dimensions of metrics: Stage (ST), Role (RT), Efficiency (ET), Quality (QT), and Distribution (PT)\n5. Generates HTML reports, cross-run comparisons, and CSV/JSON/Markdown exports\n\nThe current version is **v5.1**, which features:\n- LiteLLM Proxy as the single authoritative token data source\n- Native CLI fallback parsing\n- Reconciliation mechanism to correct api_calls inflation\n- Zero-fabricated-data guarantee (dry-run mode only prints prompts)\n- Run isolation (workspace, model, auth, logs)\n- Parallel benchmark support (up to 6 concurrent models)\n\n### 7. Existing Benchmark Results\n\nThere are **15 benchmark runs** in `results/runs/v5.1/` across multiple tool/model combinations:\n- 4 runs: `claude-code` with `claude-sonnet-4`\n- Multiple runs: `opencode-cli` with various models (qwen3.6-plus, glm-4.7, glm-5, kimi-k2.5, MiniMax-M2.5, qwen3.5-plus)\n\nThere are also older runs from v1.0 through v4.0 in `results/runs/`.\n</task_result>","metadata":{"sessionId":"ses_2857a3093ffeUKIVE8cM3B3RaD","model":{"modelID":"qwen3.6-plus","providerID":"alibaba-cn"},"truncated":false},"title":"Explore agentcube project structure","time":{"start":1775877082985,"end":1775877182190}}}}
