{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775877186017,"sessionID":"ses_2857a4700ffe1IXDyt1nODT0cT","part":{"id":"prt_d7a875e5f0010LWIp5sL6LyPJo","messageID":"msg_d7a875339001PW5p07J3vlyX5e","sessionID":"ses_2857a4700ffe1IXDyt1nODT0cT","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_b1a217e493fd401fa2e6e2e2","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/PLAN.md","offset":1300,"limit":150},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/PLAN.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1300:     - If `session_id` not provided:\n1301:       - Create `ControlPlaneClient`\n1302:       - Call `create_session()`\n1303:       - Handle failure: delete session, re-raise\n1304:     - Call `_init_data_plane()`\n1305:   - `_init_data_plane()`:\n1306:     - Create `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` with session_id\n1307:   - `__enter__()`: return self\n1308:   - `__exit__(exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb)`: call `stop()`\n1309:   - `stop()`:\n1310:     - Close data plane session\n1311:     - If created session: call `delete_session()`\n1312:     - Close control plane session\n1313:   - `execute_command(command, timeout=None) -> dict`: delegate to data plane\n1314:   - `run_code(code, language=\"python\") -> dict`:\n1315:     - Write timestamped `.py` file\n1316:     - Execute `python3 <file>`\n1317:   - `write_file(path, content)`: delegate\n1318:   - `upload_file(local_path, remote_path)`: delegate\n1319:   - `download_file(remote_path, local_path)`: delegate\n1320:   - `list_files(path) -> list`: delegate\n1321: \n1322: #### 68. `sdk-python/agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n1323: **Purpose**: High-level Agent Runtime client.\n1324: \n1325: **Logic**:\n1326: - Class `AgentRuntimeClient`:\n1327:   - `__init__(router_url, namespace, agent_name, session_id=None, timeout=120, connect_timeout=5.0)`:\n1328:     - Store config\n1329:     - If `session_id` not provided:\n1330:       - GET from invocation base URL\n1331:       - Read `x-agentcube-session-id` from response header\n1332:       - Raise `ValueError` if missing\n1333:     - Create `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`\n1334:   - `__enter__()`: return self\n1335:   - `__exit__(exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb)`: call `close()`\n1336:   - `close()`: close underlying session\n1337:   - `invoke(payload, timeout=None) -> dict`:\n1338:     - If no session_id: raise `ValueError`\n1339:     - Delegate to data plane\n1340: \n1341: #### 69. `sdk-python/agentcube/utils/http.py`\n1342: **Purpose**: HTTP utility functions.\n1343: \n1344: **Logic**:\n1345: - `read_token_from_file(path) -> str | None`:\n1346:   - Read file, return stripped contents\n1347:   - Handle FileNotFoundError, return None\n1348: - `create_session(timeout=120, connect_timeout=5.0) -> tuple`:\n1349:   - Create `requests.Session`\n1350:   - Mount `HTTPAdapter` with pool settings\n1351:   - Return session and timeout tuple\n1352: \n1353: #### 70. `sdk-python/agentcube/utils/utils.py`\n1354: **Purpose**: General utility functions.\n1355: \n1356: **Logic**:\n1357: - `ensure_dir(path)`: create directory if not exists\n1358: - `generate_timestamp() -> str`: ISO format timestamp\n1359: - `base64_encode(data) -> str`: standard base64 encoding\n1360: - `base64_decode(s) -> bytes`: standard base64 decoding\n1361: \n1362: #### 71. `sdk-python/agentcube/utils/log.py`\n1363: **Purpose**: Logging configuration.\n1364: \n1365: **Logic**:\n1366: - `setup_logging(level=logging.INFO)`:\n1367:   - Configure root logger with format\n1368:   - Return logger instance\n1369: \n1370: ---\n1371: \n1372: ## File Summary\n1373: \n1374: | File Count | Category |\n1375: |------------|----------|\n1376: | 10 | AR-023: Dify Plugin Manifest |\n1377: | 8 | AR-024: Dify Tool Schema |\n1378: | 5 | AR-025: PCAP Analyzer |\n1379: | 6 | AR-026: Helm Workload Manager |\n1380: | 5 | AR-027: Helm Router |\n1381: | 8 | AR-028: Helm CRDs & Volcano |\n1382: | 4 | AR-029: Dockerfiles & Makefile |\n1383: | 3 | AR-030: GitHub Actions |\n1384: | 10 | AR-031: CLI Pack/Build |\n1385: | 8 | AR-032: CLI Publish/Invoke/Status |\n1386: | 11 | AR-033: Python SDK |\n1387: | **Total: 78 files** |\n1388: \n1389: ---\n1390: \n1391: ## Implementation Phases\n1392: \n1393: ### Phase 1: Foundation (Week 1-2)\n1394: 1. **Python SDK (AR-033)**: Create core SDK clients and exceptions\n1395: 2. **Helm Chart Base (AR-026, AR-027, AR-028)**: Set up chart structure, CRDs, and base templates\n1396: 3. **Dockerfiles (AR-029)**: Create multi-stage builds for all Go binaries\n1397: \n1398: ### Phase 2: Integrations (Week 2-3)\n1399: 1. **Dify Plugin (AR-023, AR-024)**: Implement plugin manifest, provider, and tool schemas\n1400: 2. **CLI Toolkit (AR-031, AR-032)**: Build CLI commands for pack, build, publish, invoke, status\n1401: \n1402: ### Phase 3: Examples and CI/CD (Week 3-4)\n1403: 1. **PCAP Analyzer (AR-025)**: Create example FastAPI service\n1404: 2. **CI/CD Pipelines (AR-030)**: Set up GitHub Actions workflows\n1405: \n1406: ### Phase 4: Testing and Polish (Week 4-5)\n1407: 1. **Integration Tests**: End-to-end tests for all components\n1408: 2. **Documentation**: README files and guides\n1409: 3. **Performance Optimization**: Optimize bottlenecks\n1410: \n1411: ---\n1412: \n1413: ## Dependencies and Prerequisites\n1414: \n1415: ### External Dependencies\n1416: - Go 1.24+ for control plane components\n1417: - Python 3.10+ for SDK, CLI, and integrations\n1418: - Kubernetes 1.28+ cluster with CRD support\n1419: - Helm 3.x for chart installation\n1420: - Docker with Buildx for multi-arch images\n1421: - Redis 6+ for session storage\n1422: \n1423: ### Internal Dependencies\n1424: - SDK must be built before CLI and Dify plugin\n1425: - CRDs must exist before deploying Workload Manager/Router\n1426: - Helm chart must be complete before CI/CD pipelines\n1427: \n1428: ---\n1429: \n1430: ## Risk Mitigation\n1431: \n1432: ### High Priority Risks\n1433: 1. **Dify Plugin Compatibility**: Test against latest Dify version early\n1434: 2. **Kubernetes RBAC**: Verify ClusterRole permissions match actual usage\n1435: 3. **Session Management**: Ensure proper cleanup in SDK context managers\n1436: \n1437: ### Mitigation Strategies\n1438: - Implement comprehensive error handling in all clients\n1439: - Use connection pooling and timeouts for HTTP clients\n1440: - Add health checks and monitoring endpoints\n1441: - Create rollback procedures for deployments\n\n(End of file - total 1441 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"    - If `session_id` not provided:\n      - Create `ControlPlaneClient`\n      - Call `create_session()`\n      - Handle failure: delete session, re-raise\n    - Call `_init_data_plane()`\n  - `_init_data_plane()`:\n    - Create `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` with session_id\n  - `__enter__()`: return self\n  - `__exit__(exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb)`: call `stop()`\n  - `stop()`:\n    - Close data plane session\n    - If created session: call `delete_session()`\n    - Close control plane session\n  - `execute_command(command, timeout=None) -> dict`: delegate to data plane\n  - `run_code(code, language=\"python\") -> dict`:\n    - Write timestamped `.py` file\n    - Execute `python3 <file>`\n  - `write_file(path, content)`: delegate\n  - `upload_file(local_path, remote_path)`: delegate\n  - `download_file(remote_path, local_path)`: delegate","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"PLAN.md","time":{"start":1775877186006,"end":1775877186015}}}}
